gh-tech economies around the world suffer from polarized labor markets and political realities that lock in these problems, this book looks beyond the United States to other models of distributing a leading-edge economy. Lee emphasizes the active role of the state in creating frameworks to ensure that benefits are broadly shared, revealing that strong policies for innovation and mutual prosperity reinforce each other. Ultimately, Innovation for the Masses provides a vital window into alternative models that prioritize equity, the roadblocks these models present, and what other countries can learn from them going forward.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aEqualityxEconomic aspects. 0aTechnological innovationsxEconomic aspects. 0aTechnologyxSocial aspects. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economics / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079135840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520394896?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520394896423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520394896/original  a978-3-11-079135-8  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles